article.headline: Hawaii 60, Iowa St. 59
article.story: HONOLULU -- Bill Amis scored 17 points and made two free throws with 2.4 seconds left to give Hawaii a 60-59 win over Iowa State on Monday night. Amis was fouled at midcourt by Craig Brackins on Hawaii's inbounds pass from Adhar Mayen. Brackins had made one of two free throws to give Iowa State a 59-58 lead with 2.6 seconds remaining. Petras Balocka scored 15 points, Roderick Flemings had 12 and Mayen added 10 for the Rainbow Warriors (2-2). Diante Garrett scored 26 points to lead Iowa State (3-1). His attempt from halfcourt hit the left side of the backboard as time expired. Brackins added 10 points. Hawaii used a late 7-0 run to tie the game 58-58 on Balocka's basket with 40 seconds to go. Brackins was then fouled on his attempted putback.
